==Greek==
===Noun===
'''θείον'''  (''plural:'' uncountable)
# (''archaic''): [[sulfur]], especially in the context of [[fire and brimstone]]
#: ''The word '''theion''' translated "brimstone" is exactly the same word '''theion''' which means "divine."'' Rev. Charles H. Pridgeon, ''Is Hell Eternal or Will God's Plan Fail?'' (1931) [http://www.godstruthfortoday.org/Library/pridgeon/IsHellEternal011.htm]
# (''archaic''): the [[divine]], especially a divine fire
#: ''Divinum, in Greek is '''theion''', Divine. This term in Scripture: 1. Sometimes notes the divine essence, or God-head itself, to '''theion''' heinai homioi ("that the God head is like to" -- Acts 17:29).'' ''Extracts from Jus Divinum'' (1996)[http://www.naphtali.com/jusextrc.htm]

